> Perfect for kids and grown-ups alike, this Central American Style Chicken Rice Bowl
> is sure to become a new family favourite. Our easy tips and tweaks will help you
> create a dish that's to everyone's tastes! For little ones, set aside some plain
> mayo and marinate some chicken without the spice mix.

== Rice ==

Pour the @water{200%ml} into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @Basmati rice{100%g}, @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling,
turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered)
and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice
will continue to cook in its own steam).

== Tomato Salsa ==

Meanwhile, cut the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Zest and halve the @lime{1}. Roughly chop the @coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

In a #medium bowl{}, add the tomato chunks, half the coriander and half the lime
juice. Drizzle with @oil{}, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mix to combine, then set aside
your salsa.

== Chipotle Mayo ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @mayonnaise{32%g}, @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less
if you'd prefer things milder), @honey{1%tbsp} and @water{1%tbsp}.

== Baby Gem Salad ==

Trim the @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice.

In another medium bowl, add the sliced baby gem, a squeeze of lime juice and drizzle
of oil. Season with salt and pepper, toss to combine, then set aside.

> Making this kid friendly? Set aside some plain mayo for little ones.

== Chicken ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

In another medium bowl, add the @British chicken thighs{3}, @Central American style
spice mix{1%sachet}, and garlic. Drizzle with oil and season with salt and pepper.
Rub to coat. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken
and its packaging.

> Making this kid friendly? Marinate some chicken without the spice mix.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, lay the chicken thighs flat in the pan. Fry until browned on each side
and cooked through, ~{13-15%minutes}. Turn every 2-3 mins. IMPORTANT: The chicken
is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, cut the chicken widthways into 2cm slices.

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{}, stir through the lime zest and remaining coriander,
then share the zesty rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the baby gem salad, chicken and tomato salsa. Drizzle over the chipotle
mayo to finish.

Enjoy!